data.title: Princes and Princesses: the show at the cinema, an adventure to (re)discover with your family
data.meta_description: The film 'Princes and Princesses: The Show at the Movies', based on Michel Ocelot's tale, offers a poetic immersion through light and shadow, music and song. Not to be missed, from April 5, 2023, for poetry lovers.
data.text:
This film adaptation of the show Princes and Princesses promises to be a real enchantment for lovers of tales, animation and poetry. An appointment not to be missed for all those who wish to escape for the time of a movie session and dive into a wonderful universe. See you on April 5, 2023 to discover this nugget.

Princes and Princesses: The Motion Picture Show will be released in theaters on April 5, 2023. The film of this show is eagerly awaited by storytelling fans. The audience is immersed in a poetic and enchanting universe, where traditional tales are reinvented with a modern touch.

Legrand Bemba-Debert has managed to restore all the magic and beauty of Michel Ocelot 's tales by staging talented actors. The film offers an immersive visual and sound experience, where the play of shadows and lights blend harmoniously with the music and songs.

Princes and Princesses: The Motion Picture Show is a film that delights young and old alike, offering an immersion into a fairy tale world where morality and wisdom are emphasized. The audience will discover tales from elsewhere and be carried away by the emotion and beauty of the stories.

Synopsis of Princes and Princesses: The Show at the Movies

The film of the show Princes and Princesses, adapted from the tales of Michel Ocelot, the father of Kirikou. A journey into an imaginary world, full of poetry. Four wonderful stories where fairies, queens, princes and princesses meet. The troupe of actors, musicians, dancers and singers brings to life in four scenes, made of shadow plays and light, to bewitching African, Japanese, Egyptian and Persian tales.
